This paper is about generating informative responses in dialogue generation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computer science (cs). The paper proposes a deep attentional latent variable model that incorporates extra knowledge to generate diverse and informative responses. 

Based on the content of the paper, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which specifically deals with NLP and its applications. The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a variational generation model suggests a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which focuses on neural networks and their applications. Finally, the paper involves a joint attention mechanism, which is a common technique in cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with searching for and retrieving information from large datasets.
